reviewText: Hey kids you all know there still two more Avenger movies, right. I get the convenience of the double pack and all.  Myself I like to watch all the MCU movies in order. Plus with two other movies coming out yet, if in was going with boxed sets in would want all of them.... but thats just me.  : )

Great value for getting both movies on Blu-ray. Movies will play on any blu-ray player since they're region free. Would definitely recommend if you're looking to save a few bucks. The movies looked great too quality wise.
Beautiful 3D movie!

Why pay the same price per film, when you can have both for the price of one?  I don't feel I need to say much, I mean come on, it's the Avengers, Earth's mightiest heroes, and if you're a fan of Marvel, you've been keeping up with the MCU, then why not add both of these to your library?  Both are fun films, and yes, both have flaws as any film does, but the fun and action outweighs that in my opinion.  Do yourself a favor and Assemble . . . . I swear I had something for this.

Great deal! Region free is an excellent way to save money and get products not available in the US. Product is exactly what I wanted. My only wish is that it came in a slimmer case, but thats just not-picking.

Avengers Assemble is just another name for The Avengers. I thought there was a movie I had missed but instead I got one I already own. Five stars for the movies themselves but buyer beware on which movies you actually get.
